result.name: Din Tai Fung

reviews.text: The food here does not disappoint. We've been here a few times and their shrimp fried rice is excellent. So as their dumplings which burst with broth as you open it. So be careful and don't  shove an entire dumpling straight into your mouth. You could get burnt! Also recommended with fried rice is the beans and minced pork. This is an excellent combination. We've been there at different times of the evening. The last time we went we got there at 6:45 and were seated immediately. This was the first time that happened because we usually end up waiting quite a while. But that's also since we otherwise get there around 7:30. So if you can go earlier, the higher the chance of being seated and ordering your food immediately.

Fantastic little spot to pop by if you're in Hong Kong and want to go for dumplings. 
We went for some chicken and pork dumplings. Both of which were delicious. We also went for some fried pork chop and noodle soup which was good but relatively plain. 
We got there around 12 on a Sunday and were seated straight away (we were expecting a wait!). Service was Swift and friendly and by the time we left at about 1 the place was heaving and people were waiting outside. 
If you're looking for this restaurant you need to go inside the shopping centre and up to the 3rd floor. The directions on Google maps are a little tricky!

One Michelin star Taiwanese restaurant with a very tasteful menu.
Their dim sum options are great and very tasty. We really enjoyed all the things we tried. I  strongly recommend their steamed dumplings.

Staff are professional and attentive. 

The restaurant can get rather busy in the evenings but it is spacious enough.
Definitely recommended, one of the best dinners we had in Hong Kong.

This restaurant is in East side of Canton Road.  Google GPS is not perfect - I hope I can save u 10 min of walking around.  Look for the Chow Sang Sang entrance.  The mall is called Silvercord with a purple color (see my photos).  Take escalators to 3rd floor.  Very good dining experience.  Top experience. The dumplings had the thinnest skin ever but the soup was still in there. Double check your markings. The truffles dumplings may be a bit over the top - I cannot say I know the difference.  BTW no need to tip ! Don’t carry your bad American habits here - a 10% charge is already built in.

Very nice Taiwanese dim sum, dumplings and noodles. Very good allergy details available, comfortable high chairs for children and quick service. Good clean toilets with super effective air-conditioning making it a bit cold. Food was delicious, must have signature dish is dumplings with soup in them, dipped in soya and vinegar. Also try Angus beef with ginger and spring onion.

reviews.text: Went there tor dinner and it really didn’t disappoint! The pigeon was flavourful, crispy and succulent. The shrimp toast was light and crunchy. There’s also a wide variety of interesting dim sums to choose from as well!

I absolutely love this place! They have multiple locations and I have been to the others also. All location taste really good! I like the TST location the best because it's close to all the shopping and you can come here for a quick lunch. There's usually a wait, especially during peak hours, but I don't remember ever waiting for more than 30 minutes. 

The food comes out relatively fast, especially if you order small bites such as bao and dimsums. They also add different menu items seasonally so keep that in mind! 

I got the dessert platter which let you choose 3 different desserts from the list. It was nice since I was able to try multiple things. I also recommending getting the sample dimsum with 5 different dumplings! The fusion of using non traditional ingredients was amazing. We also got the drunken shrimp which was good but will not recommend getting here because there's nothing special about it.
traditional dish in modern way. very tasty
The environment is not bad and convenient but the food is alright... Can be better

This is not the traditional dim-sum you will find in a Cantonese restaurant. The food is not just tasty but also looks cute. Some dim-sum are more traditional than the others while they are all touched up to become a bit different from their original, either in taste or in shapes, or sometimes both.

reviews.text: Went there tor dinner and it really didn’t disappoint! The pigeon was flavourful, crispy and succulent. The shrimp toast was light and crunchy. There’s also a wide variety of interesting dim sums to choose from as well!
特式唐餐館,餸菜小巧,味道可口。
晚上walkin入座後限1.5小時要結帳，味道不錯，有很多新款菜式，份量小，價格可接受，可多叫幾款菜式一同分享，最出色是冰鎮咕嚕肉，外冰內脆，必食，流心包軟綿綿又不過甜，可作完美甜品句號
有些份量比較少，有的是正常量，自己叫時要留意，味道方面都幾好，服務員態度尚可
地方夠大坐得舒服，美味食品，甜品精緻
